                      ! described in the following steps, which are listed in
                      ! the order that they should be performed:
                      !
            ! Step 1: ! IGW_SPINUP = 0
                      !    This value is used whenever groundwater spin-up is not 
                      !    being performed, prepared, or utilized.  This includes
                      !    a multi-year climate simulation from which surface 
                      !    climate statistics can be extracted to force the
                      !    groundwater spin-up simulation.  For that climate
                      !    simulation, history files should be written monthly.
                      !
            ! Step 2: ! IGW_SPINUP = 1
                      ! RUNTYPE = 'PLOTONLY'
                      !    These values are used together to instruct OLAM to read
                      !    in a set of history files at 1-month intervals (from
                      !    the climate simulation described in Step 1) and write
                      !    a set of 12 files, one for each month, of monthly mean
                      !    surface climate conditions.  If the input history
                      !    files span multiple years, modify the commented-out
                      !    templates in subroutines olam_run and copy_plot to
                      !    combine multiple years of history files for each
                      !    calendar month.  The input history files are
                      !    specified with NPLT_FILES and PLT_FILES. For 
                      !    multiple-year climate simulations, list files for a
                      !    given month together in PLT_FILES, e.g.,
                      !       NL%PLT_FILES =
                      !          './hist/clim4-H-2001-01-01-000000.h5',
                      !          './hist/clim4-H-2002-01-01-000000.h5',
                      !          './hist/clim4-H-2003-01-01-000000.h5',
                      !          './hist/clim4-H-2004-01-01-000000.h5',
                      !          './hist/clim4-H-2001-02-01-000000.h5',
                      !          './hist/clim4-H-2002-02-01-000000.h5',
                      !          './hist/clim4-H-2003-02-01-000000.h5',
                      !          './hist/clim4-H-2004-02-01-000000.h5',
                      !          './hist/clim4-H-2001-03-01-000000.h5',
                      !          etc.
                      !    The output file names use the same prefix as the
                      !    input file names, but the identifier is changed from
                      !    'H' to 'SN', and the generic year of 0000 is assigned
                      !    to each monthly file.  An additional single file is written
                      !    with the same prefix and identifier 'GN' and contains
                      !    the grid configuration information of the 'SN' files. 
                      !
            ! Step 3: ! IGW_SPINUP = 1
                      ! RUNTYPE = 'MAKEGRID'
                      !    These values are used together to instruct OLAM to
                      !    set up atmosphere and surface grids that will be used
                      !    for the groundwater spin-up simulation.  This grid
                      !    configuration must be identical to that of any follow-on
                      !    simulation that will use the spun-up soil water and
                      !    temperature as an initial condition.  The only caveat is
                      !    that the spin-up simulation will generally have fewer
                      !    soil levels so that they will be vertically thicker for
                      !    numerical stability.  However, this is done automatically
                      !    in the code, and the settings of NZG, LANDGRID_DZTOP, and
                      !    LANDGRID_DEPTH must be identical between the spin-up and
                      !    follow-on simulations.
                      !
            ! Step 4: ! IGW_SPINUP = 1
                      ! RUNTYPE = 'INITIAL' (but with optional history restarts)
                      !    These values are used together to instruct OLAM to input
                      !    the 'SN' and 'GN' surface climate files described in 
                      !    Step 2 and perform the long-term groundwater spin-up
                      !    simulation.  Names of the 'SN' and 'GN' files are
                      !    hardwired in mem_sfcnud.f90 and can be changed there if
                      !    necessary.  The sfcgrid horizontal grid spacing of the
                      !    spin-up simulation need not be the same as the previous
                      !    climate simulation (from Step 1), and if they are
                      !    different, the spin-up simulation will horizontally
                      !    interpolate from the surface climate files.  However,
                      !    the horizontal and vertical spacing of the sfcgrid and
                      !    soil layers must be specified in OLAMIN identically to
                      !    their specification in any subsequent simulation that
                      !    uses the spin-up results to initialize the soil model.
                      !
            ! Step 5: ! IGW_SPINUP = 2
                      ! RUNTYPE = 'MAKEGRID'
                      !    These values are used together to instruct OLAM to
                      !    set up atmosphere and surface grids that will be used
                      !    for the subsequent simulation that uses the spun-up
                      !    groundwater.  The grid configurations specified for
                      !    this step must be identical with those in Step 3.  
                      !    The only reason that Step 5 is required is to produce
                      !    a sfcgfile that will not have the reduced NZG of 
                      !    Steps 3 and 4.  The atmosphere gridfile generated
                      !    will be identical with that generated in Step 3.
                      !    (Step 5 could just as well use IGW_SPINUP = 0.)
                      ! 
            ! Step 6: ! IGW_SPINUP = 2
                      ! RUNTYPE = 'INITIAL' (but with optional history restarts)
                      !    These values are used together to instruct OLAM to
                      !    initialize its soil and lake model with the results
                      !    of the spin-up simulation performed in Step 4.  The
                      !    path/name of the spin-up simulation's final history
                      !    file must be specified in GW_SPINUP_HISTFILE, and
                      !    the path/name of the sfcgfile from Step 3 must be
                      !    specified in GW_SPINUP_SFCGFILE.  Apart from this
                      !    form of initialization, this simulation is identical
                      !    to a normal simulation with IGW_SPINUP = 0.

